[{'companyId': 1038, 'companyName': 'Deloitte', 'companyUsername': 'deloitte', 'companyURL': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/deloitte/', 'companyLogo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQGNtpblgQpJoQ/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1662120928214/deloitte_logo?e=1737590400&v=beta&t=MMXn-r2-lKI-ZM0F5sGJ46ExwQyxFwcw3j_MPNJ4QCk', 'companyIndustry': 'Management Consulting', 'companyStaffCountRange': '10001+', 'title': 'Vulnerability Management Senior Specialist', 'multiLocaleTitle': {'en_US': '', 'es_ES': 'Vulnerability Management Senior Specialist'}, 'multiLocaleCompanyName': {'en_US': '', 'es_ES': 'Deloitte'}, 'location': 'Santiago Metropolitan Region, Chile', 'description': 'As a Vulnerability Management Senior Specialist, I have played a pivotal role in safeguarding our client’s environment against potential security threats and vulnerabilities.

2. Vulnerability Assessment: I perform in-depth vulnerability assessments to gauge the potential impact of identified vulnerabilities and prioritize mitigation efforts accordingly.

3. Collaboration with Cyber Threat Intelligence: My role involves close collaboration with the Cyber Threat Intelligence team to detect potential threat actors targeting our industry and to monitor threat groups exploiting Zero-Day vulnerabilities. 4. Vulnerability Impact Investigation: I conduct thorough investigations into recently published vulnerabilities, assessing their potential impact on our clients and formulating proactive strategies to mitigate risks.

5. Compliance Scanning: I execute compliance scans and generate detailed reports to ensure our clients adheres to industry and regulatory standards, thereby guaranteeing data security and compliance.

6. Client Support: I provide essential support to our clients in establishing and improving their Vulnerability Management and Patch Management programs, enhancing their security posture and ensuring they are well-prepared to face evolving threats.

educations:
[{'start': {'year': 2021, 'month': 3, 'day': 0}, 'end': {'year': 2022, 'month': 12, 'day': 0}, 'fieldOfStudy': 'Artificial Intelligence', 'degree': 'Master´s degree', 'grade': '', 'schoolName': 'Catholic University of Chile', 'description': '', 'activities': '', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/school/ucatolica/', 'schoolId': '399270'}, {'start': {'year': 2009, 'month': 0, 'day': 0}, 'end': {'year': 2015, 'month': 0, 'day': 0}, 'fieldOfStudy': 'Computer Science Engineering (Ingenieria Civil informática)', 'degree': 'Computer Science Engineer', 'grade': '', 'schoolName': 'Pontificia Universidad Catolica de Valparaiso', 'description': 'Undergraduate thesis: "Prediction of the number of foreign tourists who will arrive to the country in the next 12 months through SARIMA and Autoregressive Artificial Neural Networks"
• I collected and harmonized the data obtained from the annual and semi-annual publications of INE's tourist activity.
• I did different studies to the data such as the trend, seasonality, seasonality, autocorrelation of the time series, among others.
• I searched and iterated in order to find the best SARIMA configuration based on the AIC index.
• I programmed the autoregressive neural network in Matlab, and iterated to find the configuration that gave the least mean square error through the Levenberg-Marquardt training algorithm.
• I studied the residuals of the models to verify that they are normally distributed and not autocorrelated, to validate the model used.
